[Exodus 19:25](../../../bib/kjv/exo019.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">exo 19:25</span></span>

So Moses

The Mosaic Covenant,

\(1\) given to Israel

\(2\) in three divisions, each essential to the others, and together
forming the Mosaic Covenant, namely: the Commandments, expressing the
righteous will of God ([Exo 20:1-26](../../../bib/kjv/exo020.htm#001).md)
the "judgments," governing the social life of Israel; ([Exo
21:1-](../../../bib/kjv/exo021.htm#001.md); ([Exo
24:11](../../../bib/kjv/exo024.htm#011).md) and the "ordinances," governing
the religious life of Israel; ([Exo
24:12](../../../bib/kjv/exo024.htm#012).md); ([Exo
31:18](../../../bib/kjv/exo031.htm#018).md). These three elements form "the
law," as that phrase is generically used in the New Testament (for
example) ([Mat 5:17](../../../bib/kjv/mat005.htm#017).md); ([Mat
5:18](../../../bib/kjv/mat005.htm#018).md). The Commandments and the
ordinances formed one religious system. The Commandments were a
"ministry of condemnation" and of "death" ([Co2
3:7-9](../../../bib/kjv/co2003.htm#007).md) the ordinances gave, in the
high priest, a representative of the people with Jehovah; and in the
sacrifices a "cover" (see "Atonement,"

(See Scofield) - ([Lev 16:6](../../../bib/kjv/lev016.htm#006).md)

